Discussion written to `discussion.md`. Summary: 3 of 5 criteria pass (chaos recovered, R² > 0.9999, LC monotonically improving), 1 fails (λ₂ is an order of magnitude too negative across all runs, breaking the ~30% spectrum match), and 1 is unevaluable (SW1 not computed). The optimal LC weight landed at 1e-5, far below the hypothesized 1e-3–1e-1 range, suggesting partial observability shifts the invertibility–prediction tradeoff significantly.
